100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 13, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing issues of disarmament and international peace, amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, discussions around the ongoing economic recovery from the post-war recession continued to dominate headlines, with many experts expressing cautious optimism. Meanwhile, in China, the Nationalist government faced increasing resistance from warlords, complicating efforts to unify the country.
